Currently our robot is going for a four note auto but the trajectories won’t run if they’re put inside a parallel command group, however the command will never finish so the command group never ends. Here’s some of the code:

return new ParallelCommandGroup(
middleIntakeCmd,
new RunIntake(m_intake, m_index));

With this the code will execute but the robot will not move. If we just run the command or put it in a sequential command group it works with no errors. What can be done to troubleshoot this? For out trajectories and swerve controller commands we’re using code from the max swerve Java template.

You should use a ParallelDeadlineGroup, which ends when the first command ends, or a ParallelRaceGroup, which ends when any one of its commands ends.

For our auto this year we used all ParallelDeadlineGroups that ended when the path ended.
